Options
Arguments - Type - Definition
* braceline - boolean - If true a new line character will be inserted after
opening curly braces and before closing curly
braces. Default is false.
* bracepadding - boolean - Inserts a space after the start of a contain and
before the end of the container in JavaScript if the
contents of that container are not indented; such
as: conditions, function arguments, and escaped
sequences of template strings. Default is false.
* braces - string - If lang is 'javascript' and mode is 'beautify' this
determines if opening curly braces will exist on the
same line as their condition or be forced onto a new
line. Defaults to 'knr'.
Accepted values: knr, allman
* color - string - The color scheme of the reports. Default is shadow.
Accepted values: default, canvas, shadow, white
* comments - string - If mode is 'beautify' this will determine whether
comments should always start at position 0 of each
line or if comments should be indented according to
sthe code. Default is 'indent'.
Accepted values: indent, noindent
* commline - boolean - If a blank new line should be forced above comments
in markup. Default is false.
* compressedcss - boolean - If CSS should be beautified in a style where the
properties and values are minifed for faster reading
of selectors. Default is false.
* conditional - boolean - If true then conditional comments used by Internet
Explorer are preserved at minification of markup.
Default is false.
* content - boolean - If true and mode is 'diff' this will normalize all
string literals in JavaScript to 'text' and all
content in markup to 'text' so as to eliminate some
differences from the HTML diff report. Default is
false.
* context - number - This shortens the diff output by allowing a
specified number of equivalent lines between each
line of difference. Defaults to an empty string,
which nullifies its use.
* correct - boolean - Automatically correct some sloppiness in JavaScript.
The default is 'false' and it is only applied during
JavaScript beautification.
* crlf - boolean - If line termination should be Windows (LF) format.
Unix (LF) format is the default.
* cssinsertlines - boolean - Inserts new line characters between every CSS code
block. Default is false.
* csvchar - string - The character to be used as a separator if lang is
'csv'. Any string combination is accepted. Defaults
to a comma ','.
* diff - string - The file to be compared to the source file. This is
required if mode is 'diff'.
* diffcli - boolean - If true only text lines of the code differences are
returned instead of an HTML diff report. Default is
false.
* diffcomments - boolean - If true then comments will be preserved so that both
code and comments are compared by the diff engine.
* difflabel - string - This allows for a descriptive label for the diff
file code of the diff HTML output. Defaults to new'.
* diffspaceignore - boolean - If white space only differences should be ignored
by the diff tool. Default is false.
* diffview - string - This determines whether the diff HTML output should
display as a side-by-side comparison or if the
differences should display in a single table column.
Defaults to 'sidebyside'.
Accepted values: sidebyside, inline
* dustjs - boolean - If the provided markup code is a Dust.js template.
Takes a boolean and defaults to false.
* elseline - boolean - If elseline is true then the keyword 'else' is forced
onto a new line in JavaScript beautification.
Defaults to false.
* endcomma - boolean - If there should be a trailing comma in JavaScript
arrays and objects.
* endquietly - string - Determine if terminal logging should be allowed or
suppressed. The value 'quiet' eliminates terminal
logging and the value 'log' forces it to appear.
Accepted values: quiet, log, empty string
* force_attribute - boolean - If all markup attributes should be indented each
onto their own line. Default is false.
* force_indent - boolean - If lang is 'markup' this will force indentation upon
all content and tags without regard for the creation
of new text nodes. Default is false.
* help - string - This list of argument definitions. The value is
unnecessary and is required only to pass in use of
the parameter.
* html - boolean - If lang is 'markup' this will provide an override so
that some tags are treated as singletons and not

start tags, such as '
' opposed to '
'.
* inchar - string - The string characters to comprise a single
indentation. Any string combination is accepted.
Defaults to space ' '.
* inlevel - number - How much indentation padding should be applied to
JavaScript beautification? Default is 0.
* insize - number - The number of characters to comprise a single
indentation. Defaults to '4'.
* jsscope - string - If 'html' JavaScript beautification produces HTML
formatted output coloring function scope and
variables to indicate scope depth and inheritance.
The value 'report' is similar to the value 'html',
except that it forms the entirety of an HTML
document. Default is 'none', which just returns
beautified JavaScript in text format.
Accepted values: none, report, html
* lang - string - The programming language of the source file.
Defaults to auto.
Accepted values: auto, markup, javascript, css, html, csv, text
* langdefault - string - The fallback option if lang is set to 'auto' and a
language cannot be detected.
Accepted values: markup, javascript, css, html, csv, text
* methodchain - string - Whether consecutive JavaScript methods should be
chained onto a single line of code instead of
indented. Default is 'indent'.
Accepted values: chain, indent, none
* miniwrap - boolean - Whether minified JavaScript should wrap after a
specified character width. This option requires a
value from option 'wrap'.
* mode - string - The operation to be performed. Defaults to 'diff'.
* diff - returns either command line list of
differences or an HTML report
* beautify - beautifies code and returns a string
* minify - minifies code and returns a string
* parse - returns an object with shallow arrays
Accepted values: diff, beautify, minify, parse
* neverflatten - boolean - If destructured lists in JavaScript should never be
flattend. Default is false.
* nocaseindent - boolean - If a case statement should receive the same
indentation as the containing switch block.
* nochainindent - boolean - If indentation should be prevent of JavaScript method
chains broken onto multiple lines. Default is false.
* noleadzero - boolean - If in CSS values leading 0s immediately preceeding a
decimal should be removed or prevented.
* objsort - string - Sorts properties by key name in JavaScript and/or
CSS. Defaults to 'js'.
Accepted values: all, css, js, markup, none
* output - string - The path of the directory, if readmethod is value
'directory', or path and name of the file to write
the output. If the directory path or file exists it
will be over written else it will be created.
* preserve - number - The maximum number of empty lines to retain.
* quote - boolean - If true and mode is 'diff' then all single quote
characters will be replaced by double quote
characters in both the source and diff file input so
as to eliminate some differences from the diff
report HTML output.
* quoteConvert - string - If the quotes of JavaScript strings or markup
attributes should be converted to single quotes or
double quotes. The default is 'none', which performs
no conversion.
Accepted values: double, single, none
* readmethod - string - The readmethod determines if operating with IO from
command line or IO from files. Default value is
'screen':
* auto - changes to value subdirectory,
file, or screen depending on the
source
* screen - reads from screen and outputs to
screen
* file - reads a file and outputs to a file
- file requires option 'output'
* filescreen - reads a file and writes to screen
* directory - process all files in the immediate
directory
* subdirectory - process all files in a directory
and its subdirectories
Accepted values: auto, screen, file, filescreen, directory,
subdirectory
* report - boolean - Determines whether a report file should be created.
The default value is true. If false reports will be
suppressed for 'beautify' and 'minify' modes if
readmethod is 'file' or 'directory'.
* selectorlist - boolean - If comma separated CSS selectors should be retained
on a single line of code.
* semicolon - boolean - If true and mode is 'diff' and lang is 'javascript'
all semicolon characters that immediately preceed
any white space containing a new line character will
be removed so as to elimate some differences from
the diff report HTML output.
* source - string - The file source for interpretation. This is required.
* sourcelabel - string - This allows for a descriptive label of the source
file code of the diff HTML output.
* space - boolean - If false the space following the function keyword
for anonymous functions is removed. Default is true.
* spaceclose - boolean - If false markup self-closing tags end with '/>' and
' />' if true. Default is false.
* style - string - If mode is 'beautify' and lang is 'markup' or 'html'
this will determine whether the contents of script
and style tags should always start at position 0 of
each line or if such content should be indented
starting from the opening script or style tag.
Default is 'indent'.
Accepted values: indent, noindent
* styleguide - string - Provides a collection of option presets to easily
conform to popular JavaScript style guides. Default
is 'none'.
Accepted values: airbnb, crockford, google, grunt, jquery,
mediawiki, meteor, yandex, none
* summaryonly - boolean - Node only option to output only number of
differences and generate no reports. Default is
false.
* tagmerge - boolean - Allows immediately adjacement start and end markup
tags of the same name to be combined into a single
self-closing tag. Default is false.
* tagsort - boolean - Sort child items of each respective markup parent
element.
* textpreserve - boolean - If text in the provided markup code should be
preserved exactly as provided. This option
eliminates beautification and wrapping of text
content. Takes a boolean and defaults to false.
* ternaryline - boolean - If ternary operators in JavaScript (? and :) should
remain on the same line. Defaults to false.
* titanium - boolean - Forces the JavaScript parser to parse Titanium Style
Sheets instead of JavaScript. Default is false.
* topcoms - boolean - If mode is 'minify' this determines whether comments
above the first line of code should be kept. Default
is false.
* varword - string - If consecutive JavaScript variables should be merged
into a comma separated list ('list') or the opposite
('each'). Default is 'none'.
Accepted values: each, list, none
* vertical - string - If lists of assignments and properties should be
vertically aligned. Default is 'js'.
Accepted values: all, css, js, none
* wrap - number - How many characters text content in markup or
strings in JavaScript can be before wrapping. The
default value is 80. A value of turns this feature
off. A value of -1 will concatenate strings in
JavaScript separated by a '+' operator. In markup
wrapping occurs on the last space character prior to
the given character width
Usage
prettydiff option1:"value" option2:"value" ...
prettydiff source:"myApplication.js" readmethod:"filescreen" mode:"beautify"
prettydiff source:"old_directory" diff:"new_directory" readmethod:"subdirectory"
